+# Chat Web Data Architecture and Performance Analysis — 2026-05-08
+
+## Scope
+
+This document captures the analysis of current Chat Web loading performance and the recommended target architecture for session, room, trace, and event persistence.
+
+No application code was changed as part of this analysis.
+
+## Executive summary
+
+The current performance problem is not that Chat Web stores text. Text storage is manageable. The problem is that navigation paths do too much work:
+
+- room changes and page refreshes call a heavy bootstrap endpoint;
+- bootstrap still depends on Pi JSONL session metadata for sessions that do not have persisted titles;
+- unread counts are calculated from event history during bootstrap;
+- active and archived sessions are too tightly coupled in list-loading behavior;
+- event data is duplicated across multiple stores;
+- large SQLite databases have significant free-page and WAL bloat.
+
+The better architecture is SQLite-centered for the web read model, with JSONL kept only as a Pi compatibility, recovery, export, or reindex source. The Web UI should never scan JSONL during normal room switching or app refresh.
+
+## Current observed data
+
+Measurements were taken against the host production state under `/root/.pibo` and Pi session files under `/root/.pi/agent/sessions`.
+
+| Item | Observed value |
+| --- | ---: |
+| Pibo sessions | 228 |
+| Main owner sessions | 225 |
+| Sessions in the main `Pibo Source` room | 222 |
+| Sessions without stored title | 106 total / 103 for main owner |
+| `web_chat_events` rows | 69,110 |
+| `chat_events` rows | 69,968 |
+| `pibo_event_stream` rows | 90,766 |
+| Pi JSONL files for `/root/code/pibo` | 195 files / ~126 MB |
+| Largest Pi JSONL file | ~4.8 MB |
+| `SessionManager.list('/root/code/pibo')` | ~2.2–3.3 s |
+| Batched unread-count query for 225 sessions | ~4.3 s |
+| Recent selected-session trace event query | ~40 ms |
+| Read model session-list query | ~3 ms |
+
+Database sizes at the time of analysis:
+
+| File | Size |
+| --- | ---: |
+| `/root/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite` | ~1.73 GB |
+| `/root/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite-wal` | ~348 MB |
+| `/root/.pibo/pibo-events.sqlite` | ~923 MB |
+| `/root/.pibo/pibo-events.sqlite-wal` | ~432 MB |
+| `/root/.pibo/pibo-sessions.sqlite` | ~209 KB |
+
+SQLite free-page counts showed substantial bloat:
+
+- `web-chat.sqlite`: about 342,665 free pages at 4 KiB each, roughly 1.4 GB reusable/free space.
+- `pibo-events.sqlite`: about 182,402 free pages at 4 KiB each, roughly 747 MB reusable/free space.
+
+This does not mean the live data is necessarily that large. It means retention/deletion has left large SQLite files that need an explicit maintenance strategy.
+
+## Current data flow
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    UI[Chat Web UI] -->|GET /api/chat/bootstrap| Bootstrap[Chat Web Bootstrap]
+    UI -->|GET /api/chat/trace| TraceAPI[Trace API]
+    UI -->|SSE /api/chat/events| EventSSE[Live Event Stream]
+
+    Bootstrap --> Auth[Better Auth Session]
+    Bootstrap --> SessionStore[Pibo Session Store<br/>pibo-sessions.sqlite]
+    Bootstrap --> RoomStore[Room Store<br/>web-chat.sqlite / pibo_rooms]
+    Bootstrap --> ReadModel[Chat Read Model<br/>web-chat.sqlite / web_chat_sessions]
+    Bootstrap --> EventLog[Chat Event Log<br/>web-chat.sqlite / chat_events]
+    Bootstrap --> Catalog[Profiles / Agents / Models / Capabilities]
+    Bootstrap --> PiJSONL[Pi Session JSONL<br/>~/.pi/agent/sessions/.../*.jsonl]
+
+    TraceAPI --> ReadModel
+    TraceAPI --> EventLog
+    TraceAPI --> PiJSONL
+    TraceAPI --> TraceBuilder[Trace Builder]
+
+    Runtime[Pibo / Pi Runtime] -->|output events| PiboEvents[pibo-events.sqlite<br/>pibo_event_stream]
+    Runtime -->|persist transcript| PiJSONL
+    Runtime -->|indexed output| ReadModel
+    Runtime -->|chat/event stream| EventLog
+
+    EventSSE --> EventLog
+    EventSSE --> UI
+```
+
+## Current bottlenecks
+
+### 1. Bootstrap is too broad
+
+`/api/chat/bootstrap` currently combines multiple concerns:
+
+- identity;
+- selected room/session resolution;
+- owner session lookup;
+- visible sessions in room;
+- read marking;
+- session indexing;
+- unread counts;
+- session node construction;
+- room tree construction;
+- agent/model/capability catalog loading.
+
+For navigation, this is too much. Room switching should not need catalog rebuilding, JSONL metadata, full unread derivation, or archived-session processing.
+
+### 2. JSONL remains on a hot path
+
+When a Pibo session lacks a stored title, `buildSessionNodes()` can fall back to Pi session metadata. That uses `SessionManager.list(cwd)`, which scans and parses JSONL session files.
+
+On the measured dataset, listing Pi sessions for `/root/code/pibo` took about 2.2–3.3 seconds. That is unacceptable in a room-switch or refresh path.
+
+The important finding is that `SessionManager.list()` is not a cheap list operation. In the Pi package implementation it effectively behaves like a full metadata scan:
+
+1. read the session directory;
+2. for every `*.jsonl` file, read the complete file;
+3. split the file into lines;
+4. parse every JSONL entry;
+5. walk all entries to compute session metadata such as `messageCount`, `firstMessage`, `modified`, `name`, and `allMessagesText`;
+6. sort all resulting sessions by modified date.
+
+That means 200 sessions are not the real problem. The problem is that listing 200 sessions can mean reading and parsing about 126 MB of transcript data. Pagination only helps if it is pushed below this scan. A paginated API that first calls `SessionManager.list(cwd)` and then slices the array still performs the expensive full scan.
+
+### 3. Unread counts are derived too late
+
+The batched unread-count query is better than per-session counting, but it is still too expensive on real data: about 4.3 seconds for 225 sessions, even when the result was zero unread messages.
+
+Unread state should be materialized or updated incrementally during event ingestion. It should not be recomputed from historical events during bootstrap.
+
+### 4. Event data is duplicated
+
+The system currently stores related event data in several places:
+
+- Pi JSONL transcript;
+- `web_chat_events` in `web-chat.sqlite`;
+- `chat_events` in `web-chat.sqlite`;
+- `pibo_event_stream` in `pibo-events.sqlite`.
+
+Some duplication is justified during migration or for recovery, but the web navigation path should read from one optimized read model.
+
+### 5. SQLite is usable, but needs discipline
+
+SQLite is suitable for this scale if used as a database:
+
+- normalized tables;
+- targeted indexes;
+- pagination;
+- small hot queries;
+- WAL/checkpoint strategy;
+- retention and vacuum strategy;
+- no large payloads in list queries.
+
+SQLite becomes problematic when large JSON payloads, duplicate event copies, and expensive aggregate queries are placed on synchronous request paths.
+
+## Architecture decision
+
+The recommended direction is:
+
+> Navigation reads projections. Trace/detail views read transcripts.
+
+Concretely:
+
+> SQLite is the primary Web read model. JSONL remains only for Pi compatibility, raw transcript recovery, export, debug, or reindexing.
+
+JSONL should not be used for:
+
+- room list loading;
+- session list loading;
+- session title lookup;
+- unread counts;
+- normal bootstrap;
+- normal room switching.
+
+SQLite should own:
+
+- rooms;
+- active/archived session indexes;
+- titles and first-message summaries;
+- last activity;
+- session status;
+- parent/origin relationships;
+- message list metadata;
+- trace event index;
+- unread/read cursors;
+- materialized counters.
+
+## Target loading model
+
+### Website refresh
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    Refresh[Website refresh] --> Bootstrap[Minimal bootstrap]
+    Bootstrap --> Identity[Identity/auth]
+    Bootstrap --> RoomList[Room list]
+    Bootstrap --> CurrentRoom[Current room]
+    Bootstrap --> FirstPage[First page of active sessions]
+    FirstPage --> UI[Render app shell]
+
+    UI --> Catalog[Lazy agent/model/capability catalog]
+    UI --> Unread[Lazy or materialized unread counters]
+    UI --> Trace[Selected-session trace only]
+```
+
+### Room switch
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    RoomClick[Select room] --> Query[GET /rooms/:id/sessions?limit=50]
+    Query --> DB[(SQLite)]
+    DB --> Rows[id, title, status, profile, lastActivity, unread]
+    Rows --> UI[Render session list]
+
+    UI -->|Select session| SessionQuery[GET /sessions/:id/trace?limit=200]
+    SessionQuery --> DB
+    DB --> SessionUI[Render selected session]
+```
+
+### Archive
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    NormalRoom[Normal room view] --> ActiveOnly[WHERE archived_at IS NULL]
+    ArchiveOpen[Open archive] --> ArchiveQuery[GET /rooms/:id/sessions?archived=true&limit=50]
+    ArchiveQuery --> ArchivedRows[Paginated archived sessions]
+```
+
+Archived sessions should not be loaded during normal room switching.
+
+## Proposed logical schema
+
+This is a target shape, not an implementation patch.
+
+```text
+rooms
+  id
+  owner_scope
+  name
+  type
+  parent_room_id
+  archived_at
+  created_at
+  updated_at
+
+sessions
+  id
+  pi_session_id
+  owner_scope
+  room_id
+  parent_id
+  origin_id
+  profile
+  title
+  first_message
+  status
+  archived_at
+  created_at
+  updated_at
+  last_activity_at
+
+messages
+  id
+  session_id
+  sequence
+  role
+  content_text
+  summary
+  created_at
+  compacted_at
+
+trace_events
+  id
+  session_id
+  sequence
+  type
+  status
+  summary
+  payload_preview
+  payload_id
+  created_at
+
+trace_payloads
+  id
+  session_id
+  event_id
+  payload_json_or_text
+  byte_size
+  created_at
+
+session_read_cursors
+  session_id
+  principal_id
+  last_read_sequence
+  updated_at
+
+session_counters
+  session_id
+  principal_id
+  unread_count
+  last_message_sequence
+  updated_at
+```
+
+Large tool outputs should not be included in session-list or trace-list queries. Store a summary/preview in `trace_events` and load the full payload only when the user expands it.
+
+## Recommended rules
+
+### Rule 1: Bootstrap must be small
+
+Bootstrap should return only the data required to show the app shell and current navigation state.
+
+Do not include:
+
+- all sessions;
+- archived sessions;
+- complete traces;
+- raw events;
+- full agent catalog if cached/lazy-loadable;
+- JSONL metadata;
+- historical unread derivation.
+
+### Rule 2: Session lists are paginated SQLite read-model queries
+
+The normal session-list query should look conceptually like:
+
+```sql
+SELECT id, title, status, profile, last_activity_at, unread_count
+FROM sessions
+WHERE owner_scope = ?
+  AND room_id = ?
+  AND archived_at IS NULL
+ORDER BY last_activity_at DESC
+LIMIT 50;
+```
+
+This should be a millisecond-scale operation.
+
+### Rule 3: Unread counts are materialized
+
+Unread counts should be updated when message events are ingested, not recomputed from full event history during bootstrap.
+
+### Rule 4: Trace is lazy and paginated
+
+A selected session should load an initial trace/message window, then older content on demand.
+
+Conceptual API:
+
+```text
+GET /sessions/:id/trace?limit=200
+GET /sessions/:id/trace?before=<cursor>&limit=200
+GET /trace-events/:id/payload
+```
+
+### Rule 5: JSONL is not a navigation dependency
+
+Pi JSONL may continue to exist for compatibility and recovery, but Web UI navigation should never depend on scanning it.
+
+### Rule 6: List APIs must not parse full transcripts
+
+Any API named or used as a list operation must return from a small index. It must not parse complete JSONL transcripts for every candidate session.
+
+Bad pagination pattern:
+
+```ts
+const all = await SessionManager.list(cwd);
+return all.slice(0, 50);
+```
+
+This still reads and parses all transcripts before slicing.
+
+Good pagination pattern:
+
+```sql
+SELECT id, title, last_activity_at, status
+FROM session_index
+WHERE owner_scope = ? AND room_id = ?
+ORDER BY last_activity_at DESC
+LIMIT 50;
+```
+
+If Pi keeps a JSONL-native listing feature, it should provide a separate cheap summary API backed by an index or sidecar metadata store, for example `listSummaries()` or `listIndexed()`. The current heavy scan behavior should be explicitly named, for example `scanSessions()` or `rebuildSessionMetadata()`.
+
+## Migration plan
+
+### Phase 1: Remove hot-path JSONL dependency
+
+- Persist title, first message, modified time, session size, and relevant metadata into SQLite.
+- Backfill missing titles from JSONL once in a migration/reindex job.
+- Make bootstrap use SQLite fields only.
+
+### Phase 2: Split bootstrap
+
+- Minimal bootstrap for identity, selected room/session, and first page of active sessions.
+- Separate endpoints for catalog, archive, unread, and trace.
+- Ensure archived sessions are opt-in and paginated.
+
+### Phase 3: Materialize unread state
+
+- Update counters during event ingestion.
+- Store per-principal session or room counters.
+- Avoid historical unread aggregate queries on refresh.
+
+### Phase 4: Normalize trace/message storage
+
+- Separate message rows from trace/tool/event rows.
+- Store large payloads separately from trace summaries/previews.
+- Load full payload only on expansion.
+
+### Phase 5: Retention and SQLite maintenance
+
+- Define retention classes for live deltas, trace events, chat messages, and audit events.
+- Add controlled checkpoint/vacuum maintenance.
+- Keep backups before destructive maintenance.
+- Measure database size, WAL size, page count, and freelist count regularly.
+
+## Expected result
+
+If implemented, normal room switching should be dominated by one small indexed SQLite query plus network/render overhead. Server-side room switching should target tens of milliseconds, not seconds.
+
+The core design principle is:
+
+> The Web App must read from a small, queryable, paginated SQLite read model. Raw transcripts and full event payloads are for selected-session detail views, expansion, export, recovery, or reindexing — not for navigation.
