+# Pibo Chat Data System — Consolidated Performance Analysis
+
+Date: 2026-05-08  
+Source reports:
+
+- `chat-web-data-architecture-performance-analysis-2026-05-08.md`
+- `chat-web-data-system-performance-report-2026-05-08.md`
+- `pibo-chat-data-system-performance-report-2026-05-08.md`
+
+Scope: read-only analysis of Chat Web data flow, room/session navigation, trace loading, storage shape, and target architecture. No code, database, or gateway changes were made during the source analyses.
+
+## Executive summary
+
+Chat Web feels slow because navigation requests do too much synchronous data work. The problem is not that Pibo stores mostly text. The problem is that room switching and page refresh rebuild navigation state from mixed hot and cold data sources.
+
+The main bottlenecks are:
+
+1. `/api/chat/bootstrap` is too broad for room switching and refresh.
+2. Missing session titles keep Pi JSONL scans on the navigation path.
+3. Unread counts are recomputed from event history during bootstrap.
+4. Event data is duplicated across Pi JSONL, Chat Web event tables, Chat Web read-model tables, and the Pibo event stream.
+5. Large payloads are stored inline in hot SQLite tables.
+6. SQLite files and WAL files are bloated and need a controlled maintenance strategy.
+
+SQLite itself is not the core problem. Measured session-list queries from SQLite are fast. The slow paths come from aggregate event queries, JSONL transcript scans, large inline payloads, and an oversized bootstrap request.
+
+The target direction is:
+
+```text
+JSONL = cold transcript/export/replay source
+SQLite event log = append-only ingest source
+SQLite read models = hot UI/query path
+Payload files = large content storage
+Background indexer = transforms raw events into sessions, observations, and stats
+Optional OpenTelemetry export = future compatibility boundary
+```
+
+Navigation should read small, indexed SQLite projections. Trace/detail views may read transcripts or large payloads on demand.
+
+## Measured production-local state
+
+Measurements were taken against `/root/.pibo` and `/root/.pi/agent/sessions` on 2026-05-08.
+
+### Data volume
+
+| Metric | Value |
+|---|---:|
+| Pibo sessions | 228 |
+| Main owner sessions | 225 |
+| Sessions in room `Pibo Source` | 222 |
+| Sessions missing stored title | 106 total / 103 main owner |
+| Workspace `/root/code/pibo` sessions | 214 |
+| Workspace `/root/code/pibo` sessions missing title | 95 |
+| `chat_events` rows | 69,968 |
+| `web_chat_events` rows | 69,110 |
+| `pibo_event_stream` rows | 90,766 |
+| JSONL files for `/root/code/pibo` | 195 files / 126 MB |
+| Largest JSONL file | 4.79 MB |
+
+### Store sizes
+
+| Store | File | Size |
+|---|---|---:|
+| Chat Web DB | `/root/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite` | 1.73 GB |
+| Chat Web WAL | `/root/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite-wal` | 348 MB |
+| Pibo Event Store | `/root/.pibo/pibo-events.sqlite` | 923 MB |
+| Pibo Event WAL | `/root/.pibo/pibo-events.sqlite-wal` | 432 MB |
+| Pibo Session Store | `/root/.pibo/pibo-sessions.sqlite` | 209 KB |
+| Pibo Session WAL | `/root/.pibo/pibo-sessions.sqlite-wal` | 515 KB |
+
+### SQLite bloat indicators
+
+| Database | Page count | Freelist pages | Approx. free space |
+|---|---:|---:|---:|
+| `web-chat.sqlite` | 422,601 | 342,665 | ~1.4 GB |
+| `pibo-events.sqlite` | 225,360 | 182,402 | ~747 MB |
+
+High freelist counts mean deleted or compacted data left reusable pages inside the SQLite files. This does not by itself prove query slowness, but it increases file size, backup cost, checkpoint cost, and possible I/O/cache pressure. Any VACUUM/checkpoint work needs backups and controlled validation.
+
+### Hot-path timings
+
+| Operation | Timing |
+|---|---:|
+| `SessionManager.list('/root/code/pibo')` | 2.2-3.3 s |
+| Read and parse largest JSONL file | 108 ms |
+| `countUnreadMessagesBySession()` for 225 sessions | 4.3 s |
+| `readModel.listSessions()` | 2.8-3 ms |
+| Room tree query | 0.1 ms |
+| Read-model session precheck by ids | 2.0 ms |
+| Trace latest sequence for selected session | 0.7 ms |
+| Trace latest stream id | 0.1 ms |
+| Trace event query for selected session | ~40 ms |
+
+Interpretation:
+
+- SQLite can return normal session and room lists quickly.
+- Bootstrap becomes slow when it computes unread counts or falls back to Pi JSONL metadata.
+- Trace loading is less severe than bootstrap in the measured case, but larger sessions and cache misses can still make it noticeable.
+
+## Current data stores
+
+| Store | Location | Role | Current issue |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| Pibo Session Store | `/root/.pibo/pibo-sessions.sqlite` / `pibo_sessions` | Product-level sessions, owner, room metadata, profile, title, linked Pi session id | Fast enough; many rows miss titles |
+| Chat Web Event Log | `/root/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite` / `chat_events` | Chat event stream, read cursors, message events | Large; unread query is slow |
+| Chat Web Read Model | `/root/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite` / `web_chat_sessions`, `web_chat_events` | Session and trace read model for Chat Web | Duplicates event data; large payloads inline |
+| Pibo Event Store | `/root/.pibo/pibo-events.sqlite` / `pibo_event_stream` | Product event stream, jobs, runs | Large; high freelist count |
+| Pi JSONL Sessions | `/root/.pi/agent/sessions/.../*.jsonl` | Pi transcript, fork/replay/export source, historical metadata | Still used for navigation metadata when titles are missing |
+| Auth DB | `/root/.pibo/auth.sqlite` | Better Auth state | Not identified as bottleneck |
+| Agent Store | `/root/.pibo/chat-agents.sqlite` | Custom agent definitions | Small; not a bottleneck |
+| Room Store | `/root/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite` / `pibo_rooms` | Rooms/projects | Small; not a bottleneck |
+
+## Current data flow
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    UI[Chat Web UI] -->|GET /api/chat/bootstrap| Bootstrap[Bootstrap Handler]
+    UI -->|GET /api/chat/trace| TraceAPI[Trace API]
+    UI -->|SSE /api/chat/events| EventSSE[Live Event Stream]
+
+    Bootstrap --> Auth[Better Auth Session]
+    Bootstrap --> SessionStore[Pibo Session Store<br/>pibo-sessions.sqlite]
+    Bootstrap --> RoomStore[Room Store<br/>web-chat.sqlite / pibo_rooms]
+    Bootstrap --> ReadModel[Chat Read Model<br/>web-chat.sqlite / web_chat_sessions + web_chat_events]
+    Bootstrap --> EventLog[Chat Event Log<br/>web-chat.sqlite / chat_events]
+    Bootstrap --> Catalog[Profiles / Agents / Models / Capabilities]
+    Bootstrap --> PiJSONL[Pi JSONL Sessions<br/>~/.pi/agent/sessions/*.jsonl]
+
+    TraceAPI --> ReadModel
+    TraceAPI --> EventLog
+    TraceAPI --> PiJSONL
+    TraceAPI --> TraceBuilder[Trace Builder]
+
+    Runtime[Pibo / Pi Runtime] -->|output events| PiboEvents[pibo-events.sqlite / pibo_event_stream]
+    Runtime -->|transcript| PiJSONL
+    Runtime -->|indexed output| ReadModel
+    Runtime -->|chat event| EventLog
+
+    EventSSE --> EventLog
+    EventSSE --> UI
+```
+
+## Bootstrap hot path
+
+`/api/chat/bootstrap` currently combines navigation, indexing, unread calculation, room loading, and catalog loading.
+
+Current flow:
+
+```text
+GET /api/chat/bootstrap
+  -> require auth session
+  -> resolve requested session
+  -> select or create default room
+  -> list owner sessions
+  -> filter visible sessions by room/archive state
+  -> maybe mark selected session subtree as read
+  -> upsert session metadata into read model
+  -> compute unread counts for visible sessions
+  -> build session nodes
+       -> may call Pi SessionManager.list(cwd) if titles are missing
+  -> load room tree and room unread counts
+  -> load profiles, custom agents, model defaults, model catalog, agent catalog, capabilities
+  -> return one combined payload
+```
+
+This is too much work for a request used by initial page load and room switching. A room switch should read a compact navigation model. It should not reload capability catalogs, compute unread state from historical events, or scan JSONL metadata.
+
+## Root causes
+
+### 1. JSONL remains a hot metadata source
+
+When a Pibo session lacks a stored title, session-node construction can fall back to Pi session metadata. That path calls `SessionManager.list(cwd)`, which scans JSONL files for the workspace.
+
+On the measured system, `SessionManager.list('/root/code/pibo')` took 2.2-3.3 seconds. The cost comes from reading and parsing transcript files to compute metadata such as title, first message, message count, and modified time.
+
+Pagination does not fix this if the implementation first calls `SessionManager.list(cwd)` and then slices the array. List APIs must use a small index instead of full transcript scans.
+
+### 2. Unread counts are derived too late
+
+`countUnreadMessagesBySession()` is batched, but still took 4.3 seconds for 225 sessions. It scans event ranges, joins read cursors, filters chat-message events, uses distinct counting, and correlates assistant messages with `message_finished` events.
+
+Unread state should be materialized when events arrive or computed asynchronously. It should not block bootstrap.
+
+### 3. Bootstrap mixes unrelated concerns
+
+Identity, selected room, session list, read marking, unread counts, room tree, trace-related metadata, and catalogs travel through one endpoint. Most catalog data does not need to reload on room change.
+
+### 4. Event data is duplicated
+
+The same conceptual output exists in several places:
+
+- Pi JSONL transcript;
+- `pibo_event_stream`;
+- `chat_events`;
+- `web_chat_events`.
+
+Some duplication is useful for migration, recovery, and specialized read models. Without retention and compaction rules, it increases write pressure, storage use, WAL growth, and maintenance cost.
+
+### 5. Large payloads live inline in hot tables
+
+Large tool outputs and execution results can be hundreds of KB. Storing these payloads inline in event tables inflates database size and WAL size. It also makes list and trace queries more likely to touch large pages even when the UI only needs summaries.
+
+### 6. Synchronous request-path work blocks the server
+
+The current Node request path performs synchronous SQLite and file work. A single expensive query or JSONL scan can delay unrelated navigation requests in the same process.
+
+## Architecture decision
+
+Use this rule:
+
+> Navigation reads projections. Trace/detail views read transcripts and payloads on demand.
+
+Concretely:
+
+- SQLite should be the primary Web read model.
+- JSONL should remain for Pi compatibility, raw transcript recovery, export, debug, fork/replay, and reindexing.
+- Web navigation should never scan JSONL.
+- Large payloads should move out of hot tables and be loaded only when expanded.
+- Background indexing should transform append-only events into query-friendly session, observation, and stats tables.
+
+Do not add a large distributed observability stack now. Pibo can apply the same principles locally with SQLite, compressed payload files, and optional export later.
+
+## Target loading model
+
+### Website refresh
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    Refresh[Website refresh] --> Bootstrap[Minimal bootstrap]
+    Bootstrap --> Identity[Identity/auth]
+    Bootstrap --> RoomList[Room list]
+    Bootstrap --> CurrentRoom[Current room]
+    Bootstrap --> FirstPage[First page of active sessions]
+    FirstPage --> UI[Render app shell]
+
+    UI --> Catalog[Lazy catalog request]
+    UI --> Unread[Materialized or lazy unread counters]
+    UI --> Trace[Selected-session trace request]
+```
+
+### Room switch
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    RoomClick[Select room] --> Query[GET /rooms/:id/sessions?limit=50]
+    Query --> DB[(SQLite read model)]
+    DB --> Rows[id, title, status, profile, lastActivity, unread]
+    Rows --> UI[Render session list]
+
+    UI -->|Select session| TraceQuery[GET /sessions/:id/trace?limit=200]
+    TraceQuery --> DB
+    DB --> TraceUI[Render selected session]
+```
+
+### Archive access
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    NormalRoom[Normal room view] --> ActiveOnly[WHERE archived_at IS NULL]
+    ArchiveOpen[Open archive] --> ArchiveQuery[GET /rooms/:id/sessions?archived=true&limit=50]
+    ArchiveQuery --> ArchivedRows[Paginated archived sessions]
+```
+
+Archived sessions should not load during normal room switching.
+
+## Target local data architecture
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    Runtime[Pibo / Pi Runtime] -->|append event| RawLog[Append-only Event Log<br/>SQLite]
+    Runtime -->|optional transcript/export| JSONL[JSONL.gz / NDJSON<br/>cold storage + replay]
+
+    RawLog --> Indexer[Background Indexer]
+    Indexer --> Sessions[pibo_sessions<br/>SQLite]
+    Indexer --> Observations[pibo_observations<br/>SQLite]
+    Indexer --> Stats[pibo_session_stats<br/>SQLite]
+    Indexer --> Payloads[Payload Store<br/>.pibo/payloads/*.json.gz]
+
+    UI[Chat Web UI] -->|rooms + session list| NavAPI[Navigation API]
+    NavAPI --> Sessions
+    NavAPI --> Stats
+
+    UI -->|open trace| TraceAPI[Trace API]
+    TraceAPI --> Observations
+    TraceAPI --> Payloads
+
+    UI -->|raw/replay/export| ExportAPI[Export API]
+    ExportAPI --> RawLog
+    ExportAPI --> JSONL
+
+    Observations --> Exporter[Optional OTLP/OTel Exporter]
+    Exporter --> Observability[External backend later]
+```
+
+## Target logical schema
+
+These tables describe the intended shape, not an implementation patch.
+
+### `pibo_sessions`
+
+Navigation identity and product-level session state.
+
+```text
+id
+room_id / project_id
+owner_scope
+profile
+workspace
+pi_session_id
+parent_id
+origin_id
+title
+first_message_preview
+status
+archived_at
+created_at
+updated_at
+last_activity_at
+metadata_json
+```
+
+Requirement: title, first-message preview, and last activity must be present in SQLite. Navigation must not scan JSONL to compute them.
+
+### `pibo_observations`
+
+One structured row per trace observation/span/event.
+
+```text
+id
+session_id
+trace_id
+span_id
+parent_span_id
+sequence
+type              -- user_message, assistant_message, tool_call, tool_result, llm, error, thinking
+name              -- bash, read, edit, web_search, model_call, etc.
+status            -- running, ok, error
+started_at
+ended_at
+latency_ms
+model
+provider
+input_tokens
+output_tokens
+cost_usd
+preview_text
+payload_ref
+attributes_json
+```
+
+This supports fast timelines, error views, slow-tool views, model usage, and aggregate dashboards without scanning raw JSON payloads.
+
+### `pibo_payloads`
+
+Metadata for large content stored outside hot SQLite tables.
+
+```text
+id
+sha256
+content_type
+byte_size
+storage_path
+created_at
+retention_class
+```
+
+Move long tool outputs, full bash logs, large read results, raw provider responses, large assistant messages, and future attachments into compressed local files. Keep previews and references in hot tables.
+
+### `pibo_session_stats`
+
+Materialized navigation and aggregate state.
+
+```text
+session_id
+principal_id
+message_count
+tool_call_count
+error_count
+unread_count
+last_event_sequence
+last_message_preview
+last_activity_at
+status
+total_latency_ms
+total_tokens
+total_cost_usd
+updated_at
+```
+
+The room/session sidebar should read this table instead of counting historical events.
+
+## API shape
+
+Split the current bootstrap into smaller endpoints:
+
+```text
+/api/chat/navigation
+/api/chat/rooms
+/api/chat/sessions?roomId=...&limit=50&cursor=...
+/api/chat/catalog
+/api/chat/session/:id/trace?limit=200&cursor=...
+/api/chat/session/:id/unread
+/api/chat/trace-events/:id/payload
+```
+
+Rules:
+
+1. Bootstrap returns only identity, current room/session, room list, and first page of active sessions.
+2. Session lists are paginated SQLite read-model queries.
+3. Catalog data loads separately and can be cached.
+4. Trace data loads only for the selected session.
+5. Full payloads load only when expanded.
+6. Archived sessions are opt-in and paginated.
+
+A normal session-list query should be close to:
+
+```sql
+SELECT id, title, status, profile, last_activity_at, unread_count
+FROM session_navigation
+WHERE owner_scope = ?
+  AND room_id = ?
+  AND archived_at IS NULL
+ORDER BY last_activity_at DESC
+LIMIT 50;
+```
+
+## Recommended phases
+
+### Phase 1: Reduce navigation hot-path work
+
+- Split bootstrap into navigation, catalog, session-list, unread, and trace endpoints.
+- Keep catalog loading out of room switching.
+- Add detailed server timings for every bootstrap and trace sub-step.
+- Ensure room switching does not call `SessionManager.list()`.
+- Ensure room switching does not derive unread counts from full event history.
+
+Success criteria:
+
+- Room switch reads one small indexed SQLite projection.
+- Session list response time is milliseconds for hundreds or thousands of sessions.
+- Timing output identifies auth, session lookup, unread, JSONL, catalog, room tree, and serialization costs.
+
+### Phase 2: Materialize titles and unread counts
+
+- Backfill missing titles, first-message previews, message counts, and last activity from JSONL once.
+- Persist these fields in SQLite for active sessions.
+- Update unread counters on event append or in a background indexer.
+
+Success criteria:
+
+- Missing-title count approaches zero for active sessions.
+- `buildSessionNodes()` no longer depends on Pi JSONL during normal navigation.
+- Unread count lookup is a simple indexed read.
+
+### Phase 3: Introduce observation and stats read models
+
+- Add `pibo_observations` and `pibo_session_stats`.
+- Build them from existing event tables.
+- Use typed columns for common filters, sorts, and aggregates.
+
+Success criteria:
+
+- Trace list loads by `(session_id, sequence)`.
+- Navigation aggregates come from `pibo_session_stats`.
+- Common queries avoid JSON extraction and full payload scans.
+
+### Phase 4: Move large payloads out of hot tables
+
+- Define a payload threshold, for example 8-32 KB.
+- Store previews inline and full content in `.pibo/payloads/.../*.json.gz`.
+- Keep payload refs in observations.
+
+Success criteria:
+
+- Hot SQLite tables shrink.
+- WAL growth slows.
+- Trace queries read metadata first and payloads only on expansion.
+
+### Phase 5: Retention, compaction, and maintenance
+
+- Define retention classes for live deltas, trace events, chat messages, raw payloads, and exports.
+- Add safe WAL checkpoint and VACUUM/VACUUM INTO guidance.
+- Keep backups before destructive maintenance.
+- Track DB size, WAL size, page count, freelist count, and payload-store size.
+
+Success criteria:
+
+- DB files do not grow without bound.
+- Deleted or compacted data releases space during planned maintenance.
+- Operators can inspect storage pressure.
+
+### Phase 6: Optional OpenTelemetry-compatible export
+
+- Shape observations around trace id, span id, parent span id, timestamps, attributes, and status.
+- Add optional OTLP/OTel export later.
+- Keep local operation single-process and small-stack.
+
+Success criteria:
+
+- Pibo can export traces to external systems later without changing the internal storage model.
+- Local development does not require ClickHouse, Redis, Kafka, S3, or an OTel Collector.
+
+## What not to do now
+
+Do not immediately add required external infrastructure:
+
+- ClickHouse;
+- Redis, Kafka, NATS, or another queue;
+- S3-compatible object storage;
+- OpenTelemetry Collector as a required local dependency;
+- a large Langfuse/LangSmith-style subsystem;
+- a full rewrite of Pi transcript persistence.
+
+These tools solve real problems at larger scale. Pibo can first get most benefits through better local schemas, smaller endpoints, background indexing, payload separation, and materialized stats.
+
+## Immediate follow-up analysis tasks
+
+1. Add server timing around current bootstrap and trace handlers.
+2. Identify every navigation call site that can invoke `SessionManager.list()`.
+3. Measure unread-count query plans on larger synthetic and production-like datasets.
+4. Draft concrete migrations for `pibo_observations`, `pibo_payloads`, and `pibo_session_stats`.
+5. Define payload threshold and preview policy.
+6. Design a safe backfill path from current event tables and JSONL files.
+7. Design a compact `/api/chat/navigation` response independent from catalog and trace data.
+8. Design backup, checkpoint, and VACUUM/VACUUM INTO procedures for production-local stores.
+
+## Final conclusion
+
+The strongest evidence points to two direct bottlenecks: unread-count calculation in bootstrap and Pi JSONL session listing for missing titles. The broader issue is that Chat Web navigation still crosses raw transcript storage, event history, read models, and catalog loading in one request.
+
+Move navigation to a small SQLite read model with materialized titles, counters, and session stats. Keep JSONL and large payloads available for trace detail, replay, export, recovery, and reindexing. That should make room switching and refresh dominated by small indexed reads rather than multi-second scans and aggregate queries.
