+# Pibo Chat Data System Performance Report
+
+Date: 2026-05-08  
+Scope: Chat Web data flow, persistence, room/session navigation, trace loading, and future data-system shape.  
+Mode: Analysis only. No code, database, or gateway changes were made.
+
+## Executive summary
+
+Pibo's Chat Web UI feels slow because navigation requests do too much synchronous work. The system stores mostly text, but it stores and reprocesses that text through several layers: Pi JSONL transcripts, Pibo session SQLite rows, Chat Web event tables, Chat Web read-model tables, and the product event stream. The expensive part is not rendering one session name. The expensive part is rebuilding navigation state from mixed hot and cold data on every room switch or page refresh.
+
+The main measured bottlenecks were:
+
+1. Bootstrap performs too much work for navigation.
+2. Missing session titles keep Pi JSONL scans in the hot path.
+3. Unread-count calculation is expensive even after batching.
+4. Large payloads inflate SQLite files and WAL files.
+5. Trace/event data exists in duplicate tables, increasing storage and write pressure.
+6. SQLite itself is not the core problem, but the current schema and request path use it inefficiently.
+
+The recommended direction is a small local observability architecture:
+
+```text
+SQLite hot store
++ local compressed payload files
++ append-only event ingestion
++ background indexing
++ materialized navigation/session stats
++ optional OpenTelemetry-compatible export later
+```
+
+Do not introduce a large distributed stack now. Apply the industry principles locally: separate raw data from query data, store query fields as real columns, move large payloads out of hot tables, and keep UI navigation on precomputed read models.
+
+## Current data stores
+
+| Store | Path / table | Role | Current issue |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| Pibo Session Store | `/root/.pibo/pibo-sessions.sqlite` / `pibo_sessions` | Product-level sessions, room metadata, profile, owner, title | Fast enough; many sessions miss titles |
+| Chat Web Event Log | `/root/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite` / `chat_events` | Chat/event stream, unread state, message events | Large; unread query is slow |
+| Chat Web Read Model | `/root/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite` / `web_chat_events`, `web_chat_sessions` | Trace/read model for Chat Web | Duplicates much of `chat_events`; large payloads inline |
+| Pibo Event Stream | `/root/.pibo/pibo-events.sqlite` / `pibo_event_stream` | Product event stream | Large; high freelist count |
+| Pi JSONL Sessions | `/root/.pi/agent/sessions/.../*.jsonl` | Pi transcript, replay, historical metadata | Still used for navigation metadata when titles are missing |
+| Agent Store | `/root/.pibo/chat-agents.sqlite` | Custom agents | Small; not a bottleneck |
+| Room Store | `/root/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite` / `pibo_rooms` | Rooms/projects | Small; not a bottleneck |
+
+## Measured state on 2026-05-08
+
+Measurements were read-only and taken against `/root/.pibo` production-local data.
+
+| Metric | Value |
+|---|---:|
+| Pibo sessions | 228 |
+| Main user sessions | 225 |
+| Sessions in room `Pibo Source` | 222 |
+| Sessions with missing title | 106 total / 103 for main user |
+| JSONL files for `/root/code/pibo` | 195 files |
+| JSONL bytes for `/root/code/pibo` | 126 MB |
+| Largest JSONL file | 4.79 MB |
+| `chat_events` rows | 69,968 |
+| `web_chat_events` rows | 69,110 |
+| `pibo_event_stream` rows | 90,766 |
+| `/root/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite` | 1.73 GB |
+| `/root/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite-wal` | 348 MB |
+| `/root/.pibo/pibo-events.sqlite` | 923 MB |
+| `/root/.pibo/pibo-events.sqlite-wal` | 432 MB |
+
+SQLite freelist measurements showed heavy bloat:
+
+| Database | Page count | Freelist pages | Approx. free bytes |
+|---|---:|---:|---:|
+| `web-chat.sqlite` | 422,601 | 342,665 | ~1.4 GB |
+| `pibo-events.sqlite` | 225,360 | 182,402 | ~747 MB |
+
+## Measured hot-path timings
+
+| Operation | Timing |
+|---|---:|
+| `SessionManager.list('/root/code/pibo')` | 2.2-3.3 s |
+| Read and parse largest JSONL file | 108 ms |
+| `countUnreadMessagesBySession()` for 225 sessions | 4.3 s |
+| `readModel.listSessions()` | 2.8 ms |
+| Room tree query | 0.1 ms |
+| Read-model session precheck by ids | 2.0 ms |
+| Trace latest sequence for selected session | 0.7 ms |
+| Trace event query for selected session | 40 ms |
+
+Interpretation:
+
+- SQLite can return session lists quickly.
+- The hot path becomes slow when it does aggregate work over events or falls back to JSONL metadata scans.
+- Navigation should not call expensive event-counting or JSONL-listing paths.
+
+## Current bootstrap path
+
+The Chat Web bootstrap handler performs navigation, indexing, unread calculation, room loading, and catalog loading in one request.
+
+Relevant flow:
+
+```text
+GET /api/chat/bootstrap
+  -> require auth session
+  -> resolve requested session
+  -> select room
+  -> list owner sessions
+  -> filter visible sessions in room
+  -> maybe mark selected session subtree as read
+  -> upsert session rows into read model
+  -> compute unread counts for all visible sessions
+  -> build session nodes
+       -> may call Pi SessionManager.list(cwd) if titles are missing
+  -> load rooms
+  -> load agent/model/capability catalog
+  -> return one large bootstrap payload
+```
+
+This explains slow room switching and slow full refresh. A navigation action should read a compact navigation model. It should not recompute unread counts, scan JSONL metadata, and load capability catalogs.
+
+## Current data-flow diagram
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    UI[Chat Web UI] -->|GET /api/chat/bootstrap| Bootstrap[Bootstrap Handler]
+    UI -->|GET /api/chat/trace| TraceAPI[Trace API]
+    UI -->|SSE /api/chat/events| EventSSE[Live Event Stream]
+
+    Bootstrap --> Auth[Better Auth Session]
+    Bootstrap --> SessionStore[Pibo Session Store<br/>pibo-sessions.sqlite]
+    Bootstrap --> RoomStore[Room Store<br/>web-chat.sqlite / pibo_rooms]
+    Bootstrap --> ReadModel[Chat Read Model<br/>web-chat.sqlite / web_chat_sessions + web_chat_events]
+    Bootstrap --> EventLog[Chat Event Log<br/>web-chat.sqlite / chat_events]
+    Bootstrap --> Catalog[Profiles / Agents / Models / Capabilities]
+    Bootstrap --> PiJSONL[Pi JSONL Sessions<br/>~/.pi/agent/sessions/*.jsonl]
+
+    TraceAPI --> ReadModel
+    TraceAPI --> EventLog
+    TraceAPI --> PiJSONL
+    TraceAPI --> TraceBuilder[Trace Builder]
+
+    Runtime[Pibo / Pi Runtime] -->|output events| PiboEvents[pibo-events.sqlite / pibo_event_stream]
+    Runtime -->|transcript| PiJSONL
+    Runtime -->|indexed output| ReadModel
+    Runtime -->|chat event| EventLog
+
+    EventSSE --> EventLog
+    EventSSE --> UI
+```
+
+## Root causes
+
+### 1. JSONL is still used as hot metadata
+
+`buildSessionNodes()` can call `SessionManager.list(cwd)` when sessions lack titles. That list operation scans and parses Pi JSONL sessions. On the measured system it took 2.2-3.3 seconds for `/root/code/pibo`.
+
+JSONL is acceptable for transcript export, replay, backup, and cold storage. It should not serve the navigation UI.
+
+### 2. Unread counts are computed from event history
+
+`countUnreadMessagesBySession()` is batched, but the measured query still took 4.3 seconds for 225 sessions. The query correlates assistant messages with `message_finished` events and uses distinct counting. This is too expensive for every room switch or refresh.
+
+Unread counts should be materialized when events arrive or computed asynchronously.
+
+### 3. Bootstrap mixes unrelated concerns
+
+Bootstrap returns identity, selected session, rooms, sessions, agent profiles, custom agents, model catalog, agent catalog, and capability actions. Most of this does not need to reload when the user changes rooms.
+
+### 4. Large payloads live inline in hot SQLite tables
+
+The largest event payloads were tool execution results up to hundreds of KB. Both `chat_events` and `web_chat_events` store JSON payloads inline. This increases DB size, WAL size, query I/O, and cache pressure.
+
+### 5. Event data is duplicated
+
+The same conceptual output appears in multiple stores:
+
+- `pibo_event_stream`
+- `chat_events`
+- `web_chat_events`
+- Pi JSONL transcript
+
+Some duplication is useful during migration and for different read models. But without clear retention and compaction rules, it grows into a performance and maintenance problem.
+
+### 6. SQLite files are bloated
+
+High freelist counts show that much of the database file is free space. This does not by itself prove slow queries, but it increases file size and can worsen I/O locality. Any maintenance should be planned and tested; do not run ad hoc VACUUM on production-local stores without backup and downtime planning.
+
+## Applying industry lessons without a large stack
+
+The external report describes a common production pattern:
+
+```text
+Instrumentation
+  -> spans/events
+  -> collector/queue/batch ingestion
+  -> hot query store
+  -> cold object storage
+```
+
+For Pibo, the compact local equivalent should be:
+
+```text
+Pibo/Pi runtime
+  -> append-only local event log
+  -> background indexer
+  -> SQLite hot read models
+  -> local compressed payload files
+  -> JSONL/NDJSON export for replay/archive
+```
+
+Keep the stack small. Use the same design principles:
+
+1. Separate raw storage from query storage.
+2. Store filter/sort/group fields as columns.
+3. Store one row per observation/span/event.
+4. Move large payloads out of hot query tables.
+5. Materialize navigation aggregates.
+6. Make indexing asynchronous.
+7. Keep optional OpenTelemetry compatibility at the data-model/export boundary.
+
+## Proposed target architecture
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    Runtime[Pibo / Pi Runtime] -->|append event| RawLog[Append-only Event Log<br/>SQLite]
+    Runtime -->|optional transcript/export| JSONL[JSONL.gz / NDJSON<br/>Cold storage + replay]
+
+    RawLog --> Indexer[Background Indexer]
+    Indexer --> Sessions[pibo_sessions<br/>SQLite]
+    Indexer --> Observations[pibo_observations<br/>SQLite]
+    Indexer --> Stats[pibo_session_stats<br/>SQLite]
+    Indexer --> Payloads[Payload Store<br/>.pibo/payloads/*.json.gz]
+
+    UI[Chat Web UI] -->|rooms + session list| NavAPI[Navigation API]
+    NavAPI --> Sessions
+    NavAPI --> Stats
+
+    UI -->|open trace| TraceAPI[Trace API]
+    TraceAPI --> Observations
+    TraceAPI --> Payloads
+
+    UI -->|raw/replay/export| ExportAPI[Export API]
+    ExportAPI --> RawLog
+    ExportAPI --> JSONL
+
+    Exporter[Optional OTLP/OTel Exporter] --> Observability[External backend later<br/>ClickHouse/Langfuse/Tempo/etc.]
+    Observations --> Exporter
+```
+
+## Proposed tables
+
+### `pibo_sessions`
+
+Purpose: product-level session state and navigation identity.
+
+Important fields:
+
+```text
+id
+project_id / room_id
+owner_scope
+profile
+workspace
+pi_session_id
+title
+first_message_preview
+status
+created_at
+updated_at
+last_activity_at
+metadata_json
+```
+
+Requirement: title and first-message preview must be present in SQLite. Navigation must not scan JSONL to compute them.
+
+### `pibo_observations`
+
+Purpose: one structured row per trace observation/span/event.
+
+Suggested fields:
+
+```text
+id
+session_id
+trace_id
+span_id
+parent_span_id
+sequence
+type              -- user_message, assistant_message, tool_call, tool_result, llm, error, thinking
+name              -- bash, read, edit, web_search, model_call, etc.
+status            -- running, ok, error
+started_at
+ended_at
+latency_ms
+model
+provider
+input_tokens
+output_tokens
+cost_usd
+preview_text
+payload_ref
+attributes_json
+```
+
+This gives fast query paths for errors, slow tools, model usage, session timelines, and aggregate dashboards.
+
+### `pibo_payloads`
+
+Purpose: store large payload metadata while content lives in compressed local files.
+
+Suggested fields:
+
+```text
+id
+sha256
+content_type
+byte_size
+storage_path
+created_at
+retention_class
+```
+
+Examples of payloads to move out of hot tables:
+
+- long tool outputs
+- full bash logs
+- large read results
+- raw provider responses
+- full assistant messages above a threshold
+- attachments later
+
+### `pibo_session_stats`
+
+Purpose: materialized navigation and aggregate state.
+
+Suggested fields:
+
+```text
+session_id
+message_count
+tool_call_count
+error_count
+unread_count
+last_event_sequence
+last_message_preview
+last_activity_at
+status
+total_latency_ms
+total_tokens
+total_cost_usd
+updated_at
+```
+
+The room/session sidebar should read this table instead of counting events on demand.
+
+## Recommended phases
+
+### Phase 1: Reduce navigation hot-path work
+
+Goals:
+
+- Split bootstrap into smaller endpoints.
+- Keep catalog loading out of room switching.
+- Remove JSONL metadata scans from navigation.
+- Add detailed server timing for every navigation sub-step.
+
+Candidate endpoints:
+
+```text
+/api/chat/navigation
+/api/chat/rooms
+/api/chat/sessions?roomId=...
+/api/chat/catalog
+/api/chat/session/:id/trace
+/api/chat/session/:id/unread
+```
+
+Success criteria:
+
+- Room switch does not call `SessionManager.list()`.
+- Room switch does not count unread messages from full event history.
+- Session list response time is in milliseconds for hundreds or thousands of sessions.
+
+### Phase 2: Materialize titles and unread counts
+
+Goals:
+
+- Backfill missing titles once.
+- Persist title, first-message preview, and last activity in SQLite.
+- Maintain unread counts incrementally on event append or in a background indexer.
+
+Success criteria:
+
+- Missing-title count approaches zero for active sessions.
+- `buildSessionNodes()` no longer depends on Pi JSONL for normal navigation.
+- Unread count lookup is a simple indexed read.
+
+### Phase 3: Introduce observation and stats read models
+
+Goals:
+
+- Add `pibo_observations` and `pibo_session_stats`.
+- Build them from existing events.
+- Use them for trace timeline and navigation summaries.
+
+Success criteria:
+
+- Common queries use typed columns, not JSON extraction or full payload scans.
+- Trace list can load by `(session_id, sequence)`.
+- Navigation aggregates come from `pibo_session_stats`.
+
+### Phase 4: Move large payloads out of hot tables
+
+Goals:
+
+- Define payload threshold, for example 8-32 KB.
+- Store previews inline and full content in `.pibo/payloads/.../*.json.gz`.
+- Keep payload refs in observations.
+
+Success criteria:
+
+- Hot SQLite tables shrink.
+- WAL growth slows.
+- Trace queries read metadata first and payloads only on expansion.
+
+### Phase 5: Retention, compaction, and maintenance
+
+Goals:
+
+- Define retention classes for live deltas, trace events, chat messages, raw payloads, and exports.
+- Add safe checkpoint/VACUUM maintenance guidance.
+- Keep JSONL/NDJSON export as cold/replay format.
+
+Success criteria:
+
+- DB files do not grow without bound.
+- Deleted/compacted data releases space in planned maintenance windows.
+- Operators can inspect storage pressure.
+
+### Phase 6: Optional OpenTelemetry-compatible export
+
+Goals:
+
+- Shape observations around OTel concepts: trace id, span id, parent span id, timestamps, attributes, status.
+- Add an optional exporter later.
+- Do not require an OTel Collector for local operation.
+
+Success criteria:
+
+- Pibo can export traces to external tools without changing internal storage.
+- Local development remains single-process/small-stack.
+
+## What not to do now
+
+Do not immediately add:
+
+- required ClickHouse
+- required Redis/Kafka/NATS
+- required S3-compatible object storage
+- required OpenTelemetry Collector process
+- a large Langfuse/LangSmith clone
+- a full rewrite of Pi transcript persistence
+
+These tools solve real problems at larger scale, but Pibo can first get most of the benefit with better local schema design and background indexing.
+
+## Decision summary
+
+The right target for Pibo is not a large observability stack. It is a disciplined local data system:
+
+```text
+JSONL = cold transcript/export/replay
+SQLite event log = append-only ingest source
+SQLite read models = hot UI/query path
+Payload files = large content storage
+Background indexer = transforms events into sessions, observations, and stats
+Optional OTel export = future compatibility
+```
+
+This keeps Pibo simple while aligning it with proven observability architecture.
+
+## Immediate next analysis tasks
+
+1. Add detailed timing around the current bootstrap handler and trace handler.
+2. Identify every call site that can invoke `SessionManager.list()` during navigation.
+3. Measure unread-count query plans on larger synthetic datasets.
+4. Draft the `pibo_observations`, `pibo_payloads`, and `pibo_session_stats` schemas.
+5. Define a payload-size threshold and preview policy.
+6. Design a safe migration/backfill path from current event tables.
+7. Design a compact `/api/chat/navigation` response independent from catalog and trace data.
