+# Pibo Chat Data System Re-Architecture Implementation Plan
+
+Date: 2026-05-08  
+Status: implementation plan  
+Source report: `docs/reports/performance/data-system/pibo-chat-data-system-consolidated-analysis-2026-05-08.md`
+
+## Executive decision
+
+Rebuild the Chat Web data system around one rule:
+
+> Store full content once. Store every other copy only as a small, rebuildable index or projection.
+
+The target system makes `~/.pibo/pibo.sqlite` the product database for Pibo Sessions, rooms, event envelopes, observations, stats, cursors, runs, workflow links, and migration state. Full message/tool/provider payloads move to a content-addressed payload store under `~/.pibo/payloads`. JSONL becomes a temporary Pi compatibility artifact and export format, not the Web UI source of truth. Long term, Pibo must replace Pi JSONL writes with a Pi persistence adapter or upstream Pi extension so JSONL is no longer written by default.
+
+The Web UI must never scan JSONL, never compute unread counts from historical events during navigation, and never load large inline payloads for sidebar or room switching.
+
+## Current system findings
+
+### Storage responsibilities today
+
+| Store | Default location | Main code | Tables / files | Current responsibility | Problem |
+|---|---|---|---|---|---|
+| Pibo Session Store | `~/.pibo/pibo-sessions.sqlite` | `src/sessions/sqlite-store.ts` | `pibo_sessions` | Product-level session identity: Pibo Session ID, Pi Session ID, owner, room metadata, profile, title, parent/origin | Good boundary, but many titles are missing and room membership is stored inside metadata |
+| Chat Web DB | `~/.pibo/web-chat.sqlite` | `src/apps/chat/read-model.ts`, `src/apps/chat/event-log.ts`, `src/apps/chat/rooms.ts` | `web_chat_sessions`, `web_chat_events`, `chat_events`, `chat_session_reads`, `pibo_rooms`, `pibo_room_members` | Web read model, trace events, durable chat event stream, rooms, read cursors | Stores large JSON payloads and duplicates events in both `chat_events` and `web_chat_events` |
+| Pibo Reliability Store | `~/.pibo/pibo-events.sqlite` | `src/reliability/store.ts`, `src/apps/chat/web-app.ts` | `pibo_event_stream`, `pibo_jobs`, `pibo_dead_jobs`, `pibo_runs` | Product event stream, jobs, yielded runs, Chat Web audit copies of output events | Chat output payloads are copied again into `pibo_event_stream` |
+| Pi JSONL sessions | `~/.pi/agent/sessions/.../*.jsonl` | Pi dependency through `SessionManager`, `src/core/runtime.ts`, `src/apps/chat/trace.ts` | JSONL files | Pi transcript, fork/clone/tree/compaction/replay | Still used by Web trace and title fallback; blocks navigation and trace with file scans |
+| Workflow Store | `~/.pibo/workflows.sqlite` by default | `src/workflows/store.ts` | `workflow_runs`, `workflow_trace_events`, `workflow_session_links` | Workflow state and trace | Not the main duplication problem, but another DB to wire into selected session/project views |
+| Custom Agent Store | `~/.pibo/chat-agents.sqlite` | `src/apps/chat/agent-store.ts` | `chat_agents` | Agent Designer definitions | Separate product DB; not a performance bottleneck |
+| Better Auth DB | `~/.pibo/auth.sqlite` | Better Auth plugin | auth tables | Auth | Keep separate; Better Auth owns it |
+
+### Current write path
+
+`src/apps/chat/web-app.ts` owns the hot Chat Web indexing path through `ensureEventIndexing()`:
+
+```text
+Router output event
+  -> OutputCompactor.compact(event)
+  -> ChatEventLog.appendOutputEvent(...)        // chat_events, full payload_json
+  -> ChatWebReadModel.recordEvent(...)          // web_chat_events, full payload_json
+  -> PiboReliabilityStore.append(...)           // pibo_event_stream, full payload_json
+  -> liveListeners / SSE
+```
+
+For user sends, `sendChatMessage()` also writes `user.message.accepted` to `chat_events` before the router receives the message. Pi then writes the actual transcript into JSONL through `SessionManager` inside the Pi runtime.
+
+Result: the same conceptual turn can exist in JSONL, `chat_events`, `web_chat_events`, and `pibo_event_stream`.
+
+### Current read paths
+
+| UI / API action | Current path | Bottleneck |
+|---|---|---|
+| Initial page load / room switch | `/api/chat/bootstrap` in `src/apps/chat/web-app.ts` | Loads identity, room, selected session, owner sessions, unread counts, session nodes, rooms, catalog, models, agents, capabilities |
+| Session sidebar | `buildSessionNodes()` in `src/apps/chat/trace.ts` | Falls back to `SessionManager.list(cwd)` when `PiboSession.title` is missing |
+| Unread counts | `ChatEventLog.countUnreadMessagesBySession()` | Scans event history and correlates assistant messages with `message_finished` |
+| Trace view | `/api/chat/trace` -> `buildTraceView()` | Reads Pi JSONL transcript plus `web_chat_events`; caches only final response in memory |
+| SSE replay | `/api/chat/events` -> `ChatEventLog.listEvents()` | Replays `chat_events`; separate from `web_chat_events` trace source |
+| Debug trace | `src/debug/trace.ts` | Reads `pibo_sessions`, `web_chat_events`, and rebuilds trace using `buildTraceView()` |
+
+### Duplication matrix
+
+| Data | JSONL | `pibo_sessions` | `chat_events` | `web_chat_events` | `pibo_event_stream` | Notes |
+|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---|
+| Session identity | partial | canonical | no | partial index | no | Pibo Session Store is the correct owner |
+| Session title | maybe | should be canonical | no | no | no | Missing titles trigger JSONL scans |
+| User message text | yes | no | yes | sometimes via router echo | sometimes | Full content duplicates |
+| Assistant message text | yes | no | yes | yes | yes | Full content duplicates |
+| Tool call args/results | yes | no | yes | yes | yes | Large payload bloat |
+| Runtime trace lifecycle | partial | no | yes | yes | yes | Multiple event streams with overlapping meanings |
+| Read cursors/unread | no | no | yes | no | no | Stored in Chat Event Log, derived by history scans |
+| Room membership | no | metadata only | room id on event | no | no | Room ownership belongs in room/session projection, not JSON metadata only |
+
+The long-term target removes full-content duplication. It still permits small rebuildable projections, indexes, and previews.
+
+## Target architecture
+
+### Ownership rules
+
+1. **`sessions` owns session identity and navigation metadata.** It replaces scattered Pibo Session + Chat Web session index state.
+2. **`event_log` owns immutable event envelopes.** It stores order, type, actor, IDs, and references, not large payloads.
+3. **`payloads` owns full content.** Payload bytes are stored once, content-addressed, and referenced from events and observations.
+4. **`observations` owns the Web timeline/query projection.** It is typed, compact, and rebuildable from `event_log + payloads`.
+5. **`session_stats` and `principal_session_stats` own sidebar counters.** They are updated during ingestion or by a background indexer.
+6. **JSONL is not a Web source.** It is temporary compatibility/export only.
+7. **Old Chat Web event tables are retired.** `chat_events` and `web_chat_events` are not long-term stores.
+8. **`pibo_event_stream` no longer stores Chat output payloads.** Runs/jobs may remain, but chat output events move to the canonical event log.
+
+### Physical layout
+
+```text
+~/.pibo/pibo.sqlite
+  sessions
+  rooms
+  room_members
+  event_log
+  observations
+  session_stats
+  principal_session_stats
+  room_stats
+  principal_room_stats
+  read_cursors
+  payloads
+  indexer_offsets
+  sequence_counters
+  pibo_runs
+  pibo_jobs
+  workflow_runs
+  workflow_trace_events
+  workflow_session_links
+  migration_import_map
+
+~/.pibo/payloads/
+  sha256/ab/cd/<sha256>.json.gz
+  sha256/ef/01/<sha256>.txt.gz
+```
+
+`auth.sqlite` remains separate because Better Auth owns it. If keeping workflows/runs in separate files is safer during migration, use adapters first; the long-term product data model should still be one logical store.
+
+### Runtime flow
+
+```text
+User message
+  -> write payload text once
+  -> append event_log row: chat.user_message.accepted
+  -> update observations + session/principal stats
+  -> emit router message with same turn id
+
+Router/Pi output event
+  -> normalize PiboOutputEvent
+  -> write large args/results/text to payload store
+  -> append event_log row with payload_ref
+  -> index observation rows
+  -> update stats and unread counters
+  -> stream compact SSE frame
+
+Web navigation
+  -> query sessions + stats + rooms
+  -> no JSONL
+  -> no event-history aggregation
+
+Web timeline
+  -> query observations by session_id and sequence
+  -> include previews and payload refs
+  -> batch-load visible payloads only when needed
+```
+
+## Target schema
+
+The following schema is the target shape. The implementation may split migrations, but it must preserve these boundaries.
+
+### `sessions`
+
+Canonical Pibo Session identity and navigation metadata.
+
+```sql
+CREATE TABLE sessions (
+  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
+  pi_session_id TEXT UNIQUE,
+  owner_scope TEXT NOT NULL,
+  room_id TEXT,
+  channel TEXT NOT NULL,
+  kind TEXT NOT NULL,
+  profile TEXT NOT NULL,
+  active_model_json TEXT,
+  workspace TEXT,
+  parent_id TEXT,
+  origin_id TEXT,
+  title TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'Untitled Session',
+  first_message_preview TEXT,
+  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'idle',
+  archived_at TEXT,
+  metadata_json TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',
+  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  last_activity_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  schema_version INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,
+  FOREIGN KEY(room_id) REFERENCES rooms(id),
+  FOREIGN KEY(parent_id) REFERENCES sessions(id),
+  FOREIGN KEY(origin_id) REFERENCES sessions(id)
+);
+
+CREATE INDEX idx_sessions_owner_room_active
+ON sessions(owner_scope, room_id, archived_at, last_activity_at DESC);
+
+CREATE INDEX idx_sessions_parent
+ON sessions(parent_id, last_activity_at DESC);
+
+CREATE INDEX idx_sessions_origin
+ON sessions(origin_id, last_activity_at DESC);
+```
+
+Required changes:
+
+- Move `metadata.chatRoomId` into `sessions.room_id`.
+- Keep metadata for plugin-specific values only.
+- Ensure `title`, `first_message_preview`, and `last_activity_at` are always set.
+- Keep `pi_session_id` nullable in the final architecture so Pibo can run without Pi JSONL identity once Pi persistence is replaced. During migration it remains populated.
+
+### `rooms` and `room_members`
+
+Move the current `pibo_rooms` and `pibo_room_members` from `web-chat.sqlite` into `pibo.sqlite`.
+
+```sql
+CREATE TABLE rooms (
+  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
+  owner_scope TEXT NOT NULL,
+  name TEXT NOT NULL,
+  topic TEXT,
+  type TEXT NOT NULL,
+  parent_room_id TEXT,
+  workspace TEXT,
+  archived_at TEXT,
+  retention_policy_id TEXT,
+  metadata_json TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',
+  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  FOREIGN KEY(parent_room_id) REFERENCES rooms(id)
+);
+
+CREATE TABLE room_members (
+  room_id TEXT NOT NULL,
+  principal_id TEXT NOT NULL,
+  role TEXT NOT NULL,
+  joined_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  PRIMARY KEY(room_id, principal_id),
+  FOREIGN KEY(room_id) REFERENCES rooms(id)
+);
+
+CREATE INDEX idx_rooms_owner_parent
+ON rooms(owner_scope, parent_room_id, updated_at DESC);
+```
+
+### `payloads`
+
+Payload metadata. Full bytes live outside hot SQLite pages.
+
+```sql
+CREATE TABLE payloads (
+  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
+  sha256 TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
+  storage_kind TEXT NOT NULL,       -- file | inline-small during migration only
+  storage_path TEXT,
+  content_type TEXT NOT NULL,       -- application/json, text/plain, image/png, ...
+  encoding TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'gzip',
+  byte_size INTEGER NOT NULL,
+  compressed_byte_size INTEGER,
+  preview_text TEXT,
+  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  retention_class TEXT NOT NULL,
+  ref_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'committed'
+);
+
+CREATE INDEX idx_payloads_retention
+ON payloads(retention_class, created_at);
+```
+
+Payload policy:
+
+- Store full message/tool/provider payloads once.
+- Use content-addressed paths: `~/.pibo/payloads/sha256/<first2>/<next2>/<hash>.<ext>.gz`.
+- Write files atomically: temp file -> fsync if available -> rename -> insert/commit metadata.
+- Events and observations store only `payload_ref` plus a small preview.
+- Allow `storage_kind='inline-small'` only as a transitional optimization. The final policy should prefer files for large content and may keep tiny JSON in the payload table if benchmarks show that file-per-short-message hurts timeline loading. Either way, the payload system is the one owner of full content.
+
+### `event_log`
+
+Canonical append-only event envelope.
+
+```sql
+CREATE TABLE event_log (
+  stream_id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
+  session_id TEXT,
+  session_sequence INTEGER,
+  room_id TEXT,
+  topic TEXT NOT NULL,              -- chat, runtime, workflow, run, audit
+  type TEXT NOT NULL,
+  source TEXT NOT NULL,             -- user, router, pi, pibo, workflow, system
+  actor_type TEXT,
+  actor_id TEXT,
+  turn_id TEXT,
+  event_id TEXT,
+  tool_call_id TEXT,
+  run_id TEXT,
+  workflow_run_id TEXT,
+  idempotency_key TEXT,
+  retention_class TEXT NOT NULL,
+  payload_ref TEXT,
+  preview_text TEXT,
+  attributes_json TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',
+  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  schema_version INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,
+  UNIQUE(topic, idempotency_key),
+  FOREIGN KEY(session_id) REFERENCES sessions(id),
+  FOREIGN KEY(room_id) REFERENCES rooms(id),
+  FOREIGN KEY(payload_ref) REFERENCES payloads(id)
+);
+
+CREATE UNIQUE INDEX idx_event_log_session_sequence
+ON event_log(session_id, session_sequence)
+WHERE session_id IS NOT NULL AND session_sequence IS NOT NULL;
+
+CREATE INDEX idx_event_log_session_stream
+ON event_log(session_id, stream_id);
+
+CREATE INDEX idx_event_log_room_stream
+ON event_log(room_id, stream_id);
+
+CREATE INDEX idx_event_log_type_turn
+ON event_log(session_id, type, turn_id);
+```
+
+Important: this table replaces the long-term Chat output role of `chat_events`, `web_chat_events`, and `pibo_event_stream`. It stores enough envelope data to rebuild projections but does not duplicate full payload content.
+
+### `observations`
+
+Typed Web timeline and trace projection.
+
+```sql
+CREATE TABLE observations (
+  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
+  session_id TEXT NOT NULL,
+  sequence INTEGER NOT NULL,
+  trace_id TEXT,
+  span_id TEXT,
+  parent_span_id TEXT,
+  parent_observation_id TEXT,
+  turn_id TEXT,
+  event_stream_id INTEGER,
+  kind TEXT NOT NULL,               -- user_message, assistant_message, tool_call, tool_result, reasoning, run, subagent, error, compaction
+  role TEXT,
+  name TEXT,
+  status TEXT NOT NULL,             -- running, ok, error, cancelled
+  started_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  ended_at TEXT,
+  latency_ms INTEGER,
+  model_provider TEXT,
+  model_id TEXT,
+  input_tokens INTEGER,
+  output_tokens INTEGER,
+  cost_usd REAL,
+  preview_text TEXT,
+  payload_ref TEXT,
+  attributes_json TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',
+  FOREIGN KEY(session_id) REFERENCES sessions(id),
+  FOREIGN KEY(event_stream_id) REFERENCES event_log(stream_id),
+  FOREIGN KEY(payload_ref) REFERENCES payloads(id),
+  UNIQUE(session_id, sequence)
+);
+
+CREATE INDEX idx_observations_session_sequence
+ON observations(session_id, sequence);
+
+CREATE INDEX idx_observations_session_kind_status
+ON observations(session_id, kind, status, sequence);
+```
+
+This table is rebuildable. It may duplicate small typed columns from `event_log`, but it must not duplicate full content.
+
+### `session_stats`, `principal_session_stats`, and room stats
+
+Navigation and unread data.
+
+```sql
+CREATE TABLE session_stats (
+  session_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
+  message_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+  tool_call_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+  error_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+  last_event_stream_id INTEGER,
+  last_observation_sequence INTEGER,
+  last_message_preview TEXT,
+  last_activity_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'idle',
+  total_latency_ms INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+  total_input_tokens INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+  total_output_tokens INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+  total_cost_usd REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  FOREIGN KEY(session_id) REFERENCES sessions(id)
+);
+
+CREATE TABLE principal_session_stats (
+  session_id TEXT NOT NULL,
+  principal_id TEXT NOT NULL,
+  unread_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+  last_read_stream_id INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+  last_read_at TEXT,
+  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  PRIMARY KEY(session_id, principal_id)
+);
+
+CREATE TABLE principal_room_stats (
+  room_id TEXT NOT NULL,
+  principal_id TEXT NOT NULL,
+  unread_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+  last_read_stream_id INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+  last_read_at TEXT,
+  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  PRIMARY KEY(room_id, principal_id)
+);
+```
+
+Unread must update when events are ingested or when a read cursor moves. Bootstrap must read counters from these tables only.
+
+### `indexer_offsets` and migration state
+
+```sql
+CREATE TABLE indexer_offsets (
+  indexer_name TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
+  last_stream_id INTEGER NOT NULL,
+  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL
+);
+
+CREATE TABLE migration_import_map (
+  source_store TEXT NOT NULL,
+  source_table TEXT NOT NULL,
+  source_key TEXT NOT NULL,
+  target_kind TEXT NOT NULL,
+  target_id TEXT NOT NULL,
+  imported_at TEXT NOT NULL,
+  PRIMARY KEY(source_store, source_table, source_key)
+);
+```
+
+These tables allow safe resume, backfill validation, and legacy source decommissioning.
+
+## API target
+
+Replace the all-in-one bootstrap path with small endpoints. Keep `/api/chat/bootstrap` only as a compatibility adapter during migration.
+
+| Endpoint | Purpose | Backing tables |
+|---|---|---|
+| `GET /api/chat/navigation?area=&roomId=&sessionId=&limit=&cursor=` | Identity, selected room/session, room tree, first session page | `rooms`, `sessions`, `session_stats`, `principal_*_stats` |
+| `GET /api/chat/rooms?area=&includeArchived=` | Room tree only | `rooms`, `principal_room_stats` |
+| `GET /api/chat/sessions?roomId=&limit=&cursor=&includeArchived=` | Paginated session list | `sessions`, `session_stats`, `principal_session_stats` |
+| `POST /api/chat/sessions` | Create session | `sessions`, `session_stats` |
+| `GET /api/chat/sessions/:id/timeline?limit=&cursor=&includePayloads=` | Timeline/trace rows | `observations`, `payloads` |
+| `GET /api/chat/sessions/:id/events?since=` | Debug/replay event envelopes | `event_log` |
+| `GET /api/chat/payloads/:payloadId` | Load one payload | `payloads` + file store |
+| `POST /api/chat/payloads/batch` | Load visible payloads in one call | `payloads` + file store |
+| `GET /api/chat/catalog` | Agents, models, capabilities | plugin registry, model catalog, agent store |
+| `POST /api/chat/sessions/:id/read` | Mark selected session/tree read | `principal_session_stats`, `principal_room_stats` |
+| `GET /api/chat/events?roomId=&piboSessionId=&since=` | SSE with compact frames | `event_log` for replay + live ingester |
+
+Navigation response must not include catalog, raw trace events, or full payloads.
+
+Example navigation query:
+
+```sql
+SELECT
+  s.id,
+  s.title,
+  s.profile,
+  s.active_model_json,
+  s.parent_id,
+  s.origin_id,
+  s.status,
+  s.archived_at,
+  ss.last_message_preview,
+  ss.last_activity_at,
+  COALESCE(pss.unread_count, 0) AS unread_count
+FROM sessions s
+JOIN session_stats ss ON ss.session_id = s.id
+LEFT JOIN principal_session_stats pss
+  ON pss.session_id = s.id AND pss.principal_id = ?
+WHERE s.owner_scope = ?
+  AND s.room_id = ?
+  AND s.archived_at IS NULL
+ORDER BY ss.last_activity_at DESC
+LIMIT ?;
+```
+
