+## Implementation phases
+
+### Phase 0 — Safety, inventory, and feature flags
+
+Goal: make the current state observable and protect user data before adding V2 writes.
+
+Tasks:
+
+1. Add `pibo data inventory` or extend debug CLI to report:
+   - row counts for all legacy tables;
+   - DB sizes and WAL sizes;
+   - payload-size histograms from `payload_json` columns;
+   - missing titles;
+   - sessions with missing room IDs;
+   - duplicate event candidates across stores.
+2. Add feature flags:
+   - `PIBO_DATA_V2_WRITE=0|1`
+   - `PIBO_DATA_V2_READ=off|shadow|primary`
+   - `PIBO_LEGACY_CHAT_WRITE=1|0`
+   - `PIBO_LEGACY_JSONL_READ=1|0`
+3. Add server timings for current endpoints:
+   - auth;
+   - session lookup;
+   - room lookup;
+   - unread count;
+   - JSONL metadata;
+   - catalog;
+   - session node build;
+   - trace metadata;
+   - event query;
+   - serialization.
+4. Define backup procedure:
+   - checkpoint WAL files;
+   - copy or `VACUUM INTO` legacy DBs;
+   - copy JSONL session root for migration validation.
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- We can run inventory without mutating data.
+- We know the largest payload columns and duplicate counts.
+- Backup and restore instructions exist.
+
+### Phase 1 — Add V2 store and payload store
+
+Goal: create the new storage layer without changing application behavior.
+
+Tasks:
+
+1. Implement `src/data/schema.ts` with additive migrations.
+2. Implement `PiboDataStore` connection factory around `DatabaseSync`.
+3. Implement `PayloadStore`:
+   - `writeJson(value, retentionClass)`;
+   - `writeText(text, retentionClass)`;
+   - `read(payloadId)`;
+   - `incrementRef/decrementRef`;
+   - orphan scan.
+4. Implement canonical `EventLog.append()` with idempotency and per-session sequence allocation.
+5. Implement `ObservationStore`, `NavigationStore`, and `StatsStore` with no callers yet.
+6. Add unit tests for schema creation, payload write/read/dedupe, event idempotency, and sequence ordering.
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- `npm run typecheck` passes.
+- New unit tests pass.
+- Creating V2 store does not touch legacy stores.
+
+### Phase 2 — Canonical ingestion in shadow mode
+
+Goal: write every new Chat event to V2 while legacy writes remain active.
+
+Tasks:
+
+1. Refactor `ensureEventIndexing()`:
+   - keep legacy writes;
+   - add V2 ingest after compaction;
+   - attach same `turn_id`/`event_id` to all V2 rows;
+   - write payloads once and pass refs into event envelope.
+2. Refactor `sendChatMessage()`:
+   - write user message accepted to V2 first;
+   - keep legacy `chat_events` write while flag is enabled;
+   - use the same `clientTxnId`/turn ID for dedupe.
+3. Add synchronous projector first:
+   - append `event_log`;
+   - project `observations` and stats in the same process;
+   - if projection fails, leave `indexer_offsets` behind and catch up on restart.
+4. Add startup catch-up indexer:
+   - reads `event_log` after last offset;
+   - rebuilds missing observations/stats;
+   - logs and exposes lag.
+5. Add shadow comparison endpoint/debug command:
+   - compare legacy session list vs V2 navigation;
+   - compare legacy trace vs V2 observations;
+   - compare unread counts.
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- New events appear in V2 with no duplicate full payloads.
+- Legacy UI behavior is unchanged.
+- Shadow compare reports differences with exact session/event IDs.
+
+### Phase 3 — Backfill existing data
+
+Goal: import old state into V2 once, dedupe content, and fill missing navigation metadata.
+
+Import priority:
+
+1. `pibo-sessions.sqlite/pibo_sessions` -> `sessions`.
+2. `web-chat.sqlite/pibo_rooms`, `pibo_room_members` -> `rooms`, `room_members`.
+3. `web-chat.sqlite/web_chat_events` -> `event_log` and `observations` for trace/runtime events.
+4. `web-chat.sqlite/chat_events` -> accepted/failed user messages, SSE replay events, read cursors, unread state.
+5. `pibo-events.sqlite/pibo_event_stream` -> only product events not already imported from Chat Web; do not duplicate chat output rows.
+6. JSONL -> fill missing transcript content, first messages, titles, fork/tree metadata, and validation hashes only where V2 lacks canonical rows.
+
+Dedup rules:
+
+- Payload dedupe by SHA-256.
+- Router event dedupe by `(session_id, type, turn_id, tool_call_id, assistant_index, thinking_index, event_id)`.
+- User accepted message dedupe by `(room_id, actor_id, client_txn_id)` when present, otherwise source stream id through `migration_import_map`.
+- Transcript entry dedupe by `(pi_session_id, entry_id)`.
+- Do not import live-only deltas as durable observations if a final compact event exists.
+
+Backfill tasks:
+
+1. Implement dry-run mode that prints planned rows, payload bytes, and conflicts.
+2. Implement resumable import using `migration_import_map`.
+3. Backfill titles and previews from:
+   - existing `pibo_sessions.title`;
+   - first user observation;
+   - JSONL only as a one-time legacy source.
+4. Build stats from imported observations.
+5. Validate:
+   - session counts;
+   - room counts;
+   - message counts;
+   - trace node semantic equivalence;
+   - unread counts;
+   - payload ref integrity;
+   - orphan payload count.
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- Active sessions have titles and first-message previews.
+- Navigation needs no JSONL fallback.
+- V2 timeline can render all active sessions with payload refs.
+
+### Phase 4 — New read APIs and UI cutover
+
+Goal: move the UI off bootstrap/legacy stores.
+
+Backend tasks:
+
+1. Add `GET /api/chat/navigation`.
+2. Add paginated `GET /api/chat/sessions` backed by V2; keep path but change implementation behind flag.
+3. Add `GET /api/chat/sessions/:id/timeline`.
+4. Add `GET /api/chat/payloads/:id` and batch payload endpoint.
+5. Add `GET /api/chat/catalog` and remove catalog from navigation.
+6. Keep `/api/chat/bootstrap` as adapter that composes V2 navigation + catalog only for old clients.
+
+Frontend tasks:
+
+1. Replace `getBootstrap()` as the normal room-switch path.
+2. Load catalog lazily and cache separately.
+3. Use `getSessions()` for room switches.
+4. Use `getTimeline()` for selected session.
+5. Batch-load visible payloads; avoid full payloads for collapsed tool results.
+6. Mark read through dedicated endpoint.
+7. Adjust SSE handling:
+   - event frame patches timeline and stats;
+   - room/session invalidation only when stats change;
+   - live deltas stay in memory until finalized.
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- Room switch performs one indexed V2 navigation/session query.
+- No room switch calls `SessionManager.list()`.
+- No room switch calls unread history aggregation.
+- Catalog network request is independent and cacheable.
+
+### Phase 5 — Make V2 primary and disable legacy Chat writes
+
+Goal: stop creating new duplicate chat data.
+
+Tasks:
+
+1. Set `PIBO_DATA_V2_READ=primary` in Docker worker, then dev gateway, then production.
+2. Set `PIBO_LEGACY_CHAT_WRITE=0` after shadow metrics are clean.
+3. Change `ChatEventLog` and `ChatWebReadModel` to adapters over V2 for compatibility endpoints/tests.
+4. Stop writing Chat output payloads to `pibo_event_stream`.
+5. Keep `pibo_runs` and jobs either in `pibo-events.sqlite` temporarily or migrate them into `pibo.sqlite`; do not store full chat output there.
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- New user/assistant/tool content exists once: payload store + V2 refs.
+- Legacy `chat_events` and `web_chat_events` row counts stop growing.
+- `pibo_event_stream` no longer receives `topic='pibo.output'` chat payload copies.
+
+### Phase 6 — Replace trace rebuild from JSONL with observation timeline
+
+Goal: make trace/detail rendering independent from Pi JSONL.
+
+Tasks:
+
+1. Add observation-to-trace adapter in `src/shared/trace-engine.ts`.
+2. Update `src/apps/chat/trace.ts`:
+   - primary: build from `observations`;
+   - debug: optional legacy rebuild from JSONL/events for comparison only.
+3. Persist forkable user-message entry IDs in observations during migration and future ingest.
+4. Preserve subagent links, yielded run nodes, compaction nodes, tool calls/results, reasoning, and order keys.
+5. Add trace diff tests:
+   - legacy rebuild vs V2 projection on imported fixtures;
+   - live running turn;
+   - child session updates;
+   - fork/clone controls.
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- `/api/chat/sessions/:id/timeline` and trace UI do not read JSONL.
+- Debug can still compare against JSONL while `PIBO_LEGACY_JSONL_READ=1`.
+- Normal operation works with `PIBO_LEGACY_JSONL_READ=0` except Pi runtime internals.
+
+### Phase 7 — Pi persistence adapter and JSONL decommission
+
+Goal: remove JSONL as a required write path.
+
+This is the hardest phase because `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent` currently exposes `SessionManager` behavior used by:
+
+- `src/core/runtime.ts` session creation/opening;
+- `RoutedSession` fork/clone/switch/tree operations;
+- compaction;
+- debug and replay paths.
+
+Tasks:
+
+1. Investigate Pi extension points for custom session persistence.
+2. If supported, implement `PiboSessionManagerAdapter` backed by V2 `event_log + observations + payloads`.
+3. If not supported, choose one:
+   - upstream a Pi persistence interface;
+   - fork/wrap Pi session manager locally;
+   - keep JSONL generation as a compatibility export but stop using it as source.
+4. Implement export-on-demand JSONL:
+   - `pibo session export --format jsonl`;
+   - no default continuous JSONL writes.
+5. Reimplement fork/clone/tree metadata from V2 observations/payload refs.
+6. Add end-to-end tests without JSONL persistence enabled.
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- New sessions can run, fork, clone, compact, and reopen without JSONL as primary persistence.
+- JSONL files are not written by default.
+- JSONL can be generated on demand for external compatibility.
+
+### Phase 8 — Legacy cleanup and deletion
+
+Goal: remove old tables/files and old code paths, not keep them read-only forever.
+
+Tasks:
+
+1. Ship `pibo data legacy cleanup --archive <path>`:
+   - verifies V2 import completeness;
+   - writes final backup;
+   - stops gateway requirement for old stores;
+   - optionally deletes or archives legacy DB files.
+2. Remove or shrink:
+   - `src/apps/chat/event-log.ts`;
+   - `src/apps/chat/read-model.ts`;
+   - legacy trace JSONL hot-path functions;
+   - old debug assumptions for `web_chat_events`.
+3. Update tests to target V2 first; keep only migration tests for legacy fixtures.
+4. Remove old spec requirements that say JSONL is canonical for Web trace.
+5. Run SQLite maintenance:
+   - WAL checkpoint;
+   - `VACUUM INTO` for final V2 DB;
+   - payload GC;
+   - legacy archive compression.
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- Old Chat Web DBs are not required to start the app.
+- Old event tables are not queried during normal operation.
+- The only long-term full content store is the payload system.
+
+## Performance targets
+
+| Operation | Target |
+|---|---:|
+| Room switch, 1,000 sessions | < 50 ms server-side |
+| Session list page query | < 25 ms server-side |
+| Initial navigation excluding catalog | < 100 ms server-side |
+| Timeline first 200 observations without payload expansion | < 100 ms server-side |
+| Payload batch for visible messages | < 150 ms local server-side |
+| Unread lookup | indexed read, no history scan |
+| JSONL reads during normal Web navigation | 0 |
+| Large inline payloads in hot SQLite tables | 0 above threshold |
