+
+### Integration tests
+
+- New session -> send message -> assistant/tool events -> V2 timeline renders.
+- Room switch does not call JSONL/`SessionManager.list()`; add a spy/failing mock.
+- Restart after partial index: indexer catches up.
+- SSE reconnect from V2 event stream works.
+- Fork/clone controls still work during JSONL compatibility phase.
+- Archived room/session behavior remains unchanged.
+- Agent Designer, model defaults, user skills, and catalog load independently.
+
+### Migration tests
+
+Use fixture DBs and JSONL files:
+
+- Import from legacy `pibo-sessions.sqlite` + `web-chat.sqlite`.
+- Import duplicate events from `chat_events` and `web_chat_events` once.
+- Import `pibo_event_stream` chat output only when not already present.
+- Extract large payloads and leave refs.
+- Validate no missing payload refs.
+
+### Performance tests
+
+- Synthetic 1k, 10k, and 100k session/event datasets.
+- Navigation query timings.
+- Timeline query timings.
+- Payload batch timings.
+- Indexer catch-up throughput.
+- DB/WAL size after compaction.
+
+### Required commands before production cutover
+
+```bash
+npm run typecheck
+npm run build
+npm test
+```
+
+Also run Docker worker browser smoke tests for Chat Web navigation, trace/timeline, message send, fork/clone, archive/delete, and SSE reconnect.
+
+## Deployment plan
+
+1. Develop and test only inside a Docker compute worker.
+2. Land V2 schema and shadow writes behind flags.
+3. Run importer dry-run against production-local backups, not live DBs.
+4. Enable V2 shadow write on dev gateway.
+5. Compare V2 and legacy outputs for active users/sessions.
+6. Enable V2 primary reads on dev gateway.
+7. Disable legacy chat writes on dev gateway.
+8. After dev validation, request approval for production deployment.
+9. Production rollout:
+   - backup;
+   - run migration dry-run;
+   - enable shadow;
+   - compare;
+   - switch reads;
+   - disable legacy writes;
+   - monitor;
+   - cleanup only after explicit approval.
+
+## Operational tooling to add
+
+Follow Pibo progressive CLI discovery. Add commands under a data/debug area rather than one huge help page.
+
+Suggested command surface:
+
+```text
+pibo data
+pibo data inventory
+pibo data migrate --dry-run
+pibo data migrate --apply
+pibo data verify
+pibo data payloads stats
+pibo data payloads gc --dry-run
+pibo data legacy cleanup --dry-run
+pibo debug stores
+pibo debug trace <session> --source v2|legacy|diff
+pibo debug events <session> --source v2|legacy
+```
+
+These commands must expose paths, counts, and next actions without dumping large payloads by default.
+
+## Risks and decisions
+
+### Pi JSONL dependency
+
+The final JSONL removal depends on Pi persistence extension points. Until that work is done, JSONL may still be written by Pi internals. The Web UI must ignore it first; then the runtime persistence layer can remove it.
+
+Decision needed: upstream persistence adapter vs local fork/wrapper.
+
+### Single DB vs multiple DBs
+
+A single `pibo.sqlite` simplifies joins, transactions, backups, and mental model. It also places more write traffic on one WAL. This is acceptable for local Pibo scale if payloads are outside SQLite and indexes are targeted.
+
+Decision: use one product DB for V2 unless benchmarks show WAL contention.
+
+### Payload granularity
+
+File-per-payload is clear and dedupes well. It can be inefficient for many tiny messages. The payload system may store tiny payloads inline behind the same `payload_ref` abstraction during migration, but large payloads must be file-backed.
+
+Decision needed after benchmark: always-file vs inline-small threshold.
+
+### Projections are still duplication
+
+`observations`, stats, and FTS indexes duplicate some small fields. That is intentional. They are rebuildable and do not own full content. The rule is no duplicate full payload/transcript content.
+
+### Old specs conflict with target
+
+Some current specs intentionally made JSONL canonical. This plan supersedes that for V2. Update specs before removing legacy behavior.
+
+## Definition of done
+
+The re-architecture is complete when all statements are true:
+
+1. Creating and using a Web Chat session stores full content once in the payload system.
+2. `sessions` owns all navigation metadata needed by the UI.
+3. Room switching and refresh do not read JSONL, do not scan event history, and do not load catalog data.
+4. Timeline/trace reads `observations` and payload refs, not raw JSONL.
+5. Unread counts are materialized per principal.
+6. `chat_events` and `web_chat_events` are no longer written or queried in normal operation.
+7. Chat output is no longer copied into `pibo_event_stream`.
+8. JSONL is not a required Web or Pibo source of truth; final runtime persistence no longer writes it by default.
+9. Legacy DB cleanup tooling can archive/delete old stores after verification.
+10. Tests and debug tools explain V2 state without consulting legacy stores.
