+# Safe Gateway Restart CLI Plan
+
+## Goal
+
+Prevent accidental interruption of active Pibo agent runtimes by making gateway restarts go through the Pibo CLI only. The CLI must detect active work and block unsafe restarts.
+
+## Problem
+
+The host gateway is stateful. Active agent runtimes and in-flight work can live in gateway memory. A direct restart can terminate active agents and lose in-memory work.
+
+## Desired Operator Model
+
+Operators and agents should not interact with the gateway as a system service. Documentation and scripts should direct them to the Pibo CLI instead.
+
+All agent-facing documentation must remove references to the gateway being a system service, to `systemctl`, to service units, and to any direct stop/restart mechanism. The documented model is only: there is a Pibo gateway, and the gateway can be inspected or restarted only through the Pibo CLI.
+
+Primary commands:
+
+```bash
+pibo gateway web status
+pibo gateway web restart
+pibo gateway web restart --force
+pibo gateway web doctor
+pibo gateway dev status
+pibo gateway dev restart
+pibo gateway dev doctor
+```
+
+Production and dev should use the same operator model: gateways are managed through the Pibo CLI, not through direct service/process commands.
+
+## CLI Behavior
+
+### `pibo gateway web status`
+
+Report:
+
+- gateway reachability
+- mode: dev, prod, fallback, or unknown
+- active session runtime statuses
+- sessions with `processing === true`
+- sessions with `streaming === true`
+- sessions with `queuedMessages > 0`
+- active yielded runs, if available
+
+### `pibo gateway web restart`
+
+Flow:
+
+1. Query gateway status.
+2. Query active runtime state.
+3. If active work exists, block restart.
+4. If status cannot be determined, block restart.
+5. If no active work exists, perform a controlled restart.
+
+Blocked message:
+
+```text
+Restart blocked: active agent work is running.
+Do not restart the gateway now.
+Ask the user before interrupting active sessions.
+```
+
+### Active Work Definition
+
+A restart is unsafe when any of these are true:
+
+- any session has `processing === true`
+- any session has `streaming === true`
+- any session has `queuedMessages > 0`
+- any yielded run is active/running
+- runtime status cannot be read reliably
+- gateway state is ambiguous
+
+### `pibo gateway web restart --force`
+
+Force restart should require explicit confirmation:
+
+```bash
+pibo gateway web restart --force --confirm restart-active-agents
+```
+
+Without the exact confirmation token, block the restart.
+
+### `pibo gateway dev restart`
+
+Dev gateway restarts should also go through the Pibo CLI for consistency and to remove direct service/process commands from the agent operating model.
+
+Unlike production, dev restarts do not need the active-work blocker. Dev may be restarted at any time.
+
+Expected behavior:
+
+1. Restart the dev gateway through the CLI.
+2. Print clear status and health output.
+3. Do not expose or document the underlying service/process mechanism.
+
+## Gateway Status Source
+
+Use existing or new gateway APIs to expose safe status data:
+
+- `listSessionRuntimeStatuses()`
+- active yielded run summaries
+- gateway mode
+- gateway health
+
+The CLI must be conservative. If it cannot prove the gateway is idle, it must not restart.
+
+## Deployment Script Changes
+
+Update:
+
+- `scripts/deploy-web-dev.sh`
+- `scripts/deploy-web.sh`
+
+Remove direct restart behavior from deploy scripts, including dev deploy scripts.
+
+Deploy scripts should:
+
+1. Build artifacts.
+2. Install/update deploy artifacts.
+3. Verify static/build success where possible.
+4. Print a clear final instruction.
+
+Final deploy message:
+
+```text
+Deploy complete.
+Gateway was not restarted.
+To activate this deployment, run:
+
+  pibo gateway web restart
+
+The CLI will block the restart if active agent work is running.
+```
+
+Dev deploy final message:
+
+```text
+Dev deploy complete.
+Dev gateway was not restarted.
+To activate this dev deployment, run:
+
+  pibo gateway dev restart
+```
+
+Dev restart does not need to block on active work, but it must still go through the CLI.
+
+## Documentation Changes
+
+Update `AGENTS.md` so agents do not see or use system-service operations.
+
+Delete all agent-facing hints that the gateway is implemented as a system service, can be controlled with `systemctl`, or has service unit names. Do not mention direct service restarts, service stops, service status commands, fallback service operations, or any underlying process-manager details.
+
+The agent-facing documentation should state only:
+
+```md
+## Host Gateway
+
+Pibo has host gateways. They are managed only through the Pibo CLI.
+
+Production gateway:
+
+  pibo gateway web status
+  pibo gateway web restart
+
+Dev gateway:
+
+  pibo gateway dev status
+  pibo gateway dev restart
+
+The production gateway is stateful and may contain active agent runtimes. It may need to be restarted when it is stuck, after a deployment, or after gateway configuration changes. The CLI checks for active production work and blocks unsafe restarts.
+
+The dev gateway may be restarted at any time, but it must still be restarted through the CLI for consistency.
+
+Do not use any other restart mechanism. If the CLI blocks a production restart, ask the user before interrupting active sessions.
+```
+
+Avoid explaining the underlying service mechanism in agent-facing docs. The purpose is to remove the dangerous path from the agent's available operating model.
+
+## Safety Rules
+
+The CLI must block restart when:
+
+- active sessions exist
+- active yielded runs exist
+- status calls fail
+- gateway mode is unclear
+- multiple gateway processes are detected and cannot be disambiguated
+- fallback/main state is ambiguous
+
+The CLI may restart only when it has positively established that no active work is running.
+
+## Tests
+
+Add tests for:
+
+1. restart blocks with `processing: true`
+2. restart blocks with `streaming: true`
+3. restart blocks with `queuedMessages > 0`
+4. restart blocks with active yielded runs
+5. restart blocks when status is unavailable
+6. restart succeeds when gateway is idle
+7. force restart requires exact confirmation token
+8. deploy scripts no longer call direct restart operations
+9. deploy scripts print CLI restart instructions
+
+## Migration Plan
+
+1. Implement gateway status surface if missing.
+2. Implement `pibo gateway web status`.
+3. Implement guarded `pibo gateway web restart`.
+4. Add force-confirm behavior.
+5. Implement `pibo gateway dev status/restart` without active-work blocking.
+6. Change deploy scripts to stop restarting directly.
+7. Update `AGENTS.md` and other agent-facing docs.
+8. Add tests.
+9. Validate in Docker worker.
+10. Deploy to dev without restart.
+11. Restart dev through `pibo gateway dev restart`.
+12. Use production CLI restart only when idle.
+13. Roll out to production.
+
+## Acceptance Criteria
+
+A deployment or agent action must not be able to accidentally terminate active agent runtimes.
+
+The only documented restart path is:
+
+```bash
+pibo gateway web restart
+```
+
+The dev gateway restart path is:
+
+```bash
+pibo gateway dev restart
+```
+
+No agent-facing documentation should mention system services, service unit names, `systemctl`, direct process kills, or alternative restart paths for any host gateway.
+
+The production restart command must block by default whenever active agent work may be running. The dev restart command may restart immediately, but only through the CLI.
