+## 7. Parallelization Plan
+
+### 7.1 Sequential Gate 1
+
+WP0 must happen first. It defines contracts and prevents subagents from creating incompatible APIs.
+
+### 7.2 First Parallel Batch
+
+After WP0, split work across four agents:
+
+| Agent | Package | Notes |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| A | WP1 Workflow core types/registry/validation | No persistence or UI dependency. |
+| B | WP2 Workflow persistence/trace store | Depends only on finalized type contracts. |
+| C | WP3 Project API facade | Must not modify existing Room API behavior. |
+| D | WP4 Projects tab shell | Must keep Sessions tab behavior unchanged. |
+
+### 7.3 Second Parallel Batch
+
+After WP1 and WP2 land:
+
+| Agent | Package | Notes |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| E | WP5 runner for function/user nodes | Uses registry and store. |
+| F | WP6 API/debug CLI read surface | Uses store and service contracts. |
+| G | WP4 follow-up UI extraction if needed | Only extract shared components when duplication blocks Projects. |
+
+### 7.4 Third Parallel Batch
+
+After WP4, WP5, and WP6 are stable:
+
+| Agent | Package | Notes |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| H | WP7 Projects Workflow status UI | Consumes read APIs. |
+| I | WP8 standard-project skeleton | Consumes runner and registry. |
+| J | WP9 runtime node adapter | Integrates Session Router; keep scope narrow. |
+
+### 7.5 Final Sequential Gate
+
+WP10 and WP11 should land after the skeleton flow works. They connect user decisions, runtime behavior, and UI state, so integration order matters.
+
+## 8. Subagent Work Orders
+
+Use these as copy-pasteable assignments.
+
+### Work Order A: Workflow Core
+
+Implement `src/workflows` core types, registry, and validator from `spec/spec-architecture-workflow-mvp.md`. Do not add persistence or UI. Add unit tests for duplicate definitions, invalid edges, invalid usage, terminal nodes, and retry bounds.
+
+### Work Order B: Workflow Store
+
+Implement local SQLite persistence for Workflow Runs, Workflow Trace events, and Workflow Session links. Enforce ordered append-only traces and JSON-serializable state. Add tests for create/update/list/get, trace sequence uniqueness, and main/sub Session links.
+
+### Work Order C: Project API Facade
+
+Add Project-shaped backend APIs for the Chat Web app. Keep existing Room APIs unchanged. If you wrap `PiboRoomStore`, hide Room language in Project API responses and mark the compatibility layer in comments. Add tests that existing Room APIs still work.
+
+### Work Order D: Projects Tab Shell
+
+Add a new Projects tab to Chat Web as a 1:1 copy of the Sessions tab shell and behavior. Keep the green Personal Chat row at the top of the sidebar. Replace the Rooms section below it with Projects. Copy Room-equivalent Project edit/archive/restore/delete controls. Reuse the Sessions session tree for Project Sessions, including create/select/rename/archive/restore/delete and Main/Sub-Session nesting. Reuse the selected Session terminal/transcript, session-view selector, trace controls, raw-events controls, composer, slash commands, drafts, and send behavior. Add separate Projects routes and local storage keys. Project and Project Session create/select/edit/archive/restore/delete must remain on `/projects...` routes and must not navigate to Sessions. Do not remove or rename the Sessions tab.
+
+### Work Order E: Workflow Runner
+
+Implement start/resume/discard for function and user nodes. Emit required trace events. Support deterministic transitions and bounded retries. Add tests for happy path, waiting/resume, discard, guarded transition, and retry exhaustion.
+
+### Work Order F: Workflow Debug Surface
+
+Expose list/show/trace read paths for Workflow Runs through internal service functions and debug CLI commands. Keep agent-callable tools out of scope. Make output compact and agent-discoverable.
+
+### Work Order G: Projects Workflow Status UI
+
+Add Projects UI components that display Workflow type, status, current state, retry count, main Session link, waiting prompt, and failure/discard reason. These components must wrap or sit above the normal selected Project Session surface. Reuse existing Session terminal/transcript, composer, and trace views instead of duplicating or hiding them.
+
+### Work Order H: Standard Project Workflow
+
+Register `standard-project` V1 as `session-only`. Implement its skeleton nodes and transitions. It may use function nodes first. It must reach user feedback and support completed, failed, and discarded terminal states with traceable reasons.
+
+### Work Order I: Runtime Node Adapter
+
+Add runtime-node execution through existing Pibo Session Router/profile APIs. Link main and sub Pibo Sessions to Workflow Runs. Emit runtime start/completion traces with Session ids and worker/worktree metadata when available.
+
+### Work Order J: User Feedback And E2E
+
+Wire approve, request changes, and discard actions in Projects UI. Add end-to-end checks for Sessions regression and Projects Workflow flow. Verify destructive cleanup requires explicit confirmation.
+
